urls.title: RPostgreSQL: R Interface to the 'PostgreSQL' Database System
urls.description: Database interface and 'PostgreSQL' driver for 'R'. This package provides a Database Interface 'DBI' compliant driver for 'R' to access 'PostgreSQL' database systems. In order to build and install this package from source, 'PostgreSQL' itself must be present your system to provide 'PostgreSQL' functionality via its libraries and header files. These files are provided as 'postgresql-devel' package under some Linux distributions. On 'macOS' and 'Microsoft Windows' system the attached 'libpq' library source will be used.

tweets.text: Want to learn more about transforming data from wide to long format in #Rstats? Check out the latest blog post. 📈 #datascience

So which one should you choose? It depends on your needs and preferences. If you want more flexibility and speed, go for pivot_longer(). If you prefer simplicity and ease of use, go for melt(). Both functions have their pros and cons. 🔍 #Rstats #datascience

On the other hand, melt() from the #reshape2 package is an older function that's still widely used. It's more straightforward, making it a great option for beginners. However, it offers less flexibility than pivot_longer(). 🤔 #Rstats #datascience

pivot_longer() is the newer function from the #tidyr package, offering more flexibility and speed. It allows you to melt multiple columns simultaneously and handle more complex situations. Plus, it works seamlessly with other tidyverse packages. 🙌 #Rstats #datascience

Do you need help to transform your data from wide to long format in #Rstats? 🤔 There are two popular functions for this task: pivot_longer() and melt(). But which one is the best option? Let's find out! 🔍 #datascience
